President Obama held a briefing with key officials to discuss preparations for Hurricane Sandy. He instructed FEMA Administrator Craig Fugate to ensure that federal resources are being utilized to support state and local responders along the Eastern seaboard. FEMA is working closely with other federal departments and state and local partners to prepare for the storm. They are deploying teams to potentially affected states, holding daily briefings with emergency response teams, and prepositioning resources like water and meals. The President emphasized the importance of coordination between state authorities and utility companies to address potential power outages. He directed his team to ensure that all needs are met and to keep him updated on preparations.